posts.raw_content:
Some of y’all may remember when I posted about stepping away from the corporate grind to open a restaurant. Well—we’ve officially opened the doors and it’s been amazing! That said, I’m still at my day job for now because my wife has an unexpected major surgery coming up, and we need to hang onto our insurance a little longer. She’s been running the day-to-day until she goes in for surgery, and let me tell you, she’s been a rockstar.

We’ve only been open a few weeks and we’re already doing three times what we expected. The support, the turnout—it’s been incredible, and we’re still trending up every single week.

One thing I’ve noticed being out in the real world again: the MEGA crowd is strong! I’ve seen more Trump hats and shirts than I can count—and honestly, it’s encouraging to see so many like-minded folks. One of our best servers has even earned the nickname “Trump Girl” because she rocks the gear when she’s off the clock—and yes, she’s absolutely our hardest worker. Guests wearing MAGA hats or shirts always get a warm welcome and lots of compliments.

Big thanks to everyone who’s shared words of support and advice—it’s meant a lot. I can’t wait to finally walk away from the cubicle farm for good. For now, we’re still fine-tuning things, cutting overhead where we can, and pushing to make the restaurant the best it can be.
